Rioting broke out in Toledo, Ohio after a neo-Nazi march was disrupted by counter-protestors.
The police lost control as rioters vandalized streets and set a building on fire.
Mitt Romney condemned the supremacists' presence, while a man researched a novel by posing as a white supremacist online.
The situation escalated when a masked gang member threatened the mayor, leading to clashes between protestors and police.
Despite tensions, the mayor emphasized the right to peaceful protest.
The incident highlighted racial divides and the need for community unity in the face of hate groups.
